title: Chacha Bhatija
subTitle: Teja, a widower, marries Sonia, a girl who only wants to get her hands on his inheritance. So, she creates animosity between Teja, his brother and his son.

title: Dhund
subTitle: After crashing his car on a foggy night, a man seeks help at a nearby home, where he encounters a dead man and a woman holding a gun. After hearing her sad story, he helps her hide the crime.

title: Patthar Ke Sanam
subTitle: Meena and Taruna tease their new manager Rajesh, but both fall for him. An attack on Rajesh brings his mother to town, which reveals a dark past and leads to tragedy.

title: DARNA ZAROORI HAI
subTitle: Six children lose their way in a forest in the middle of the night. Later, they reach a haunted house where an old woman challenges them to sit through a narration of six horrific stories.

title: Kshatriya
subTitle: Two royal families in Rajasthan fight annually to fulfil an age-old tradition. Unaware of the clash, their grandsons become best friends and attempt to end the family feud.

title: Bade Ghar Ki Beti
subTitle: Mala, a poor girl, marries the son of her father's employer. Things, however, take a turn for the worse when her father-in-law dies and his ruthless children show their true colours.

title: Anari
subTitle: Rama, a simpleton, is appointed as the bodyguard of Rajnandini, a rich girl. She soon falls in love with him but her brothers' violent nature gets in the way of her uniting with Rama.

title: Mr. Azaad
subTitle: Azaad, an orphan, takes to petty crime and acts like a modern-day Robin Hood. However, the death of an honest constable causes him to take stock of his actions.

title: Aankhen
subTitle: Good-for-nothing brothers Munnu and Bunnu crack elaborate practical jokes, one of which gets out of hand. As a result, Bunnu goes missing and is presumed dead while Munnu is suspected of his murder.

title: Haathkadi
subTitle: ACP Suraj, an honest policeman, swears revenge on culprits when his innocent brother is killed. However, he is soon accused of murder and is remanded to prison.

title: Hum To Mohabbat Karega
subTitle: A hotel waiter named Raju becomes entangled in danger when his attempt to impress news anchor Geeta by claiming to witness a murder leads to unexpected twists.

title: Take 2 Extraaa
subTitle: The cast and the crew involved in the production of the movie 'Piku' share their experiences and the challenges faced during filming.

title: Murder
subTitle: Simran is a lonely housewife who bumps into Sunny, her lover from her past, and the two get into a torrid affair. But when her husband finds out, he plans to end the affair as quickly as it began.

title: Dushman
subTitle: Sonia is raped and murdered by Gokul. To avenge her death, her twin sister, Naina, takes help from a retired Major Suraj Singh Rathod, a man with visual impairment, and plans to teach the murderer a lesson.

title: Gardish
subTitle: Purshottam, a policeman, wishes for his son, Shiva, to become a police inspector. However, when he gets attacked by mobsters, the latter resorts to violence and crime.

title: Andaaz
subTitle: After his sweetheart Kajal marries another man, Raj moves to Cape Town. He eventually agrees to marry Jiya but is shocked to find that she is Kajal's widowed sister-in-law.

title: Aag
subTitle: A young man seeks a fresh start in a village after enduring tragedy, only to find himself entangled in a conflict that tests his strength and sense of justice.

title: Maqsad
subTitle: Rajeshwar is the only son of a wealthy industrialist, while Tilak hails from a poor family. When Rajeshwar's father is murdered and the blame falls on Tilak, he must strive to prove his innocence.

title: Veergati
subTitle: Ajay finds it difficult to work in a corrupt society. Hence, he begins to gamble and soon finds himself helping the prostitutes who are exploited by Ekka Seth.

title: Ahankaar
subTitle: Prabhat loses his voice in an accident while trying to save his stepmother. However, his sacrifice goes unappreciated by a family largely filled with selfish and unethical people.

title: All the Best: Fun Begins
subTitle: When a wealthy sibling pays a surprise visit, two best friends struggle to keep up with the web of lies they fooled him with, in order to ensure a generous allowance.

title: Dam Sharks!
subTitle: Executives on a weekend trip find themselves in danger when they learn that a storm has caused the local river to become infested with sharks.

title: Kati Patang
subTitle: A runaway bride, Madhavi, makes a solemn vow to her dying widowed friend, Poonam, to look after the upbringing of her child.

title: Raampur Ka Lakshman
subTitle: During a journey, Kedarnath Bhargav, his wife, Laxmi, and two sons, Ram and Lakshman, get separated and subsequently, they all lead different lives.

title: Ram Balram
subTitle: Unaware of his evil intentions and his role in killing their parents, two brothers Ram and Balram fall victim to their deceitful uncle. They must unite to foil his plans of gaining wealth.

title: Mr. Natwarlal
subTitle: When Natwar's elder brother is framed for bribery, he decides to avenge his brother's humiliation and thus poses as a crime lord.

title: Aan Milo Sajna
subTitle: Savitri, a wealthy widow, refuses to leave any inheritance to Anil, her self-centred son. So, he hires a woman to pretend to be his wife in order to please his mother.

title: Ghar Ek Mandir
subTitle: Brothers Prem, Vijay and Ravi are happy, but their lives change when Prem gets killed. Ravi must save his family from an evil man, Dharampal, while Vijay is preoccupied with Sapna.

title: Haath Ki Safai
subTitle: Brothers Raju and Shankar, who are separated by fate, cross paths with each other in Mumbai when Kamini, a wealthy runaway, unintentionally barges into their lives.
